value.title: Videos, virtual events and planned trips: Biden, Obama, Pence, Trump weigh in on Georgia runoffs
value.excerpt: President Trump, his predecessor and soon-to-be successor in the White House, as well as Vice President Mike Pence, are all weighing in on Georgia’s two Jan. 5 Senate runoff elections, where the Republican majority in the chamber is up for grabs.

value.title: Iowa's contact-tracing firm helped Trump, Reynolds campaigns
value.excerpt: After facing a workforce shortage for months, Iowa has awarded an emergency $2.3 million contact-tracing contract to a company owned by a Republican Party insider

value.title: Iran pressures Biden with plan to increase underground enrichment machines
value.excerpt: Iran is raising pressure on U.S. President-elect Joe Biden with plans to install more advanced uranium-enriching centrifuges at an underground plant in breach of its deal with major powers, a U.N. nuclear watchdog report showed on Friday.

value.title: Fact check: Facebook post touting decreasing drug prices under Trump is misleading
value.excerpt: A viral claim appears to take data out of context to tout decreasing drug prices under President Donald Trump.

value.title: Trump ignores facts with claim of improper 'vote dumps'
value.excerpt: In lawsuits, tweets and a 46-minute taped diatribe, the president has promoted a false narrative about vote counting in several states.

value.title: Trump is holding out on supporting the $908 billion COVID-19 stimulus bill despite more lawmakers rallying round it
value.excerpt: After a press conference, the White House clarified that Trump does not support the $908 billion compromise bill, and instead wants a smaller one.

value.title: Biden wrestles with politics in effort to depoliticize the Justice Department
value.excerpt: Political questions from Democrats and a new Republican litmus test have suddenly become complicating factors in one of President-elect Joe Biden's most critical choices: picking a new Attorney General to lead the Justice Department out of its highly politicized era.

value.title: In race to cement legacy, Trump pushes dozens of 'midnight regulations'
value.excerpt: The Trump administration is quietly racing to solidify its legacy, fulfill campaign promises and overhaul federal regulations that could take Joe Biden years to undo.

value.title: Republican congressman tells Trump to 'delete your account' after he tweeted a 45-minute speech repeating baseless voter-fraud claims
value.excerpt: Republican Rep. Adam Kinzinger, who represents Illinois' 16th District, quote-tweeted Trump on Thursday.

value.title: Trump, Pence to campaign in Georgia as Senate runoff turnout concerns grow among GOP
value.excerpt: Mike Pence and President Donald Trump's rallies for Georgia's senators will be against a backdrop of growing concerns about GOP turnout in the Senate runoff election.

value.title: Dangerously viral: How Trump, supporters spread false claims

value.title: Roles of Trump fundraiser, Kushner's attorney were scrutinized in pardon bribe probe

value.title: Harris on her working relationship with Biden: 'We are full partners in this process'
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden and Vice President-elect Kamala Harris may have been fierce rivals in the Democratic primary, but now, as they prepare to take control of the White House, they say they are full partners who agree on how to approach the country's most pressing issues.

value.title: Biden says multiple Republican senators have called to congratulate him on election win
value.excerpt: President-elect Joe Biden revealed Thursday that "more than several" Republican senators have called to privately congratulate him on his election win, despite the fact that most of them have not publicly acknowledged his victory last month.

value.title: Does Biden think it's important Trump attend inauguration? Hear his answer
value.excerpt: In an interview with CNN's Jake Tapper, President-elect Joe Biden explains the importance of a demonstration of a peaceful transfer of power at his inauguration.

value.title: Biden on nominating diverse Cabinet: 'I'm going to keep my commitment'
value.excerpt: Joe Biden said Thursday he would keep his commitment to nominate a Cabinet that reflects America's diversity, as the President-elect faces increasing pressure to appoint Black and Latino nominees to remaining high-level Cabinet positions.

value.title: Perdue tacitly acknowledges Biden administration, despite public pronouncements
value.excerpt: In a private zoom call with the Republican Jewish Coalition obtained by The Washington Post, Sen. David Perdue (R-Ga.) referred several times to a new administration run by President-elect Joe Biden.

value.title: Romney calls Trump's leadership on Covid-19 'a great human tragedy'
value.excerpt: Republican Sen. Mitt Romney on Thursday blasted President Donald Trump's leadership -- or lack thereof -- during the deadly coronavirus pandemic as "a great human tragedy."

value.title: Kamala Harris Makes More History With All-Female Senior Staff Picks
value.excerpt: For the first time, the top three positions in the office of the vice president will be held by women -- and all serving under the first woman to hold the office.

value.title: Trump campaign, RNC raise $207.5 million since Election Day
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: The Trump campaign, the Republican National Committee, their joint-fundraising committees and President Trump’s new PAC Save America raised a whopping $207.5 million since Election Day, Fox News has learned.

value.title: Former Reagan campaign director Ed Rollins slams pro-Trump attorney as 'glorified ambulance chaser'
value.excerpt: Former Reagan campaign director Ed Rollins slammed President Trump's formal and allied legal teams on Fox News Radio's "The Brian Kilmeade Show" Thursday, at one point calling attorney Lin Wood a "glorified ambulance chaser."

value.title: Ratcliffe urges Biden to let Durham probe run its course, says more docs 'should be' declassified
value.excerpt: EXCLUSIVE: Director of National Intelligence John Ratcliffe on Thursday urged President-elect Joe Biden to allow Special Counsel John Durham's investigation into the origins of the Russia probe to run its course, while saying he hopes there will be "folks held accountable that should be."
